to life insurance, the potential of Web3 technology remains largely untapped. Our organization is at the forefront of this transformation, set to redefine how life insurance is bought, sold, and leveraged.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/seph.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Screenshot-2023-08-29-123643-300x249.jpg\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-08-29 123643\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"249\" width=\"300\" title=\"Screenshot 2023-08-29 123643\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\">\n\t<h2><strong>A Visionary Approach<\/strong><\/h2>\n\t<p>Central to our organization&#8217;s vision is the establishment of a secondary market for life insurance through the utilization of smart contracts. Consider the following scenarios:<\/p>\n<p><strong>1. Option A: Get the Surrender Value<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>This is the traditional route. However, our platform offers so much more, enabling individuals to unlock greater value from their policies.<\/p>\n<p><strong>2. Option B: Selling Above Surrender Value<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Imagine an insured individual putting their life insurance policy on the market. Interested funders, aware of the opportunity, provide capital exceeding the surrender value. The magic happens with the introduction of smart contracts. The remaining premium is calculated based on the insured&#8217;s age and life expectancy, and once the capital surpasses the surrender value, it&#8217;s transferred to the insured, minus the premium. The policy is then transferred to the holder, along with the value of the remaining premium. The holder pays the premium until the insured&#8217;s passing, at which point the death benefit is paid out. This benefit is distributed proportionally to funders who contributed capital.<\/p>\n<p><strong>3. Option C: Borrow Against Life Insurance<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Again, smart contracts make all the difference. Funders provide capital exceeding the surrender value, which is lent to the insured. If the insured pays interest, they maintain the right to claim the life insurance. If not, the policy transfers to the holder. The holder waits until the insured&#8217;s passing, at which point the death benefit is distributed, once more proportionally to funders.<\/p>\n\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/seph.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/JasperArt_2023-08-29_12.45.07_upscaled.jpg\" alt=\"JasperArt_2023-08-29_12.45.07_upscaled\" itemprop=\"image\" height=\"2048\" width=\"2048\" title=\"JasperArt_2023-08-29_12.45.07_upscaled\" onerror=\"this.style.display='none'\">\n\t<h2><strong>The Road Ahead<\/strong><\/h2>\n\t<p>In a world where innovation is key and possibilities are endless, our organization stands as the beacon of change. A chance to revolutionize an industry, unlock value, and make a lasting impact-this is the narrative we offer. Join us in shaping the future of life insurance through Web3 technology. The opportunity is compelling, the impact is immense, and the potential is limitless.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Seph- Sell Your Life Unlocking Value and Empowering Change: Revolutionizing Life Insurance with Web3 Technology Imagine a world where the traditional boundaries of life insurance are shattered, opening up new avenues for financial growth and social impact. Welcome to the innovative realm of Web3-powered life insurance, where smart contracts and decentralized networks come together to &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"\" href=\"http:\/\/seph.local\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Home<\/span> Read More &raquo;<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-mai